author: COMSOL
description: This benchmark model computes the turbulent flow field in a centrifugal blood pump. The computed wall shear stress can be used to predict damage that might occur to the blood passing through the pump under various load conditions. The model geometry is taken from FDA's Computational Round Robin and was used for several simulations under the given flow rates and pump speeds. The 2D profiles of the velocity magnitude and pressure head are in good agreement with experimental data.
label: fda_benchmark_blood_pump.mph
